{
  "id": 2733,
  "name": "Imperator Averzian",
  "description": "Imperator Averzian wages a relentless campaign, seeking not conquest, but annihilation. His entire will is bent to a singular ambition: to rend the veil between worlds and carve a breach into the Void itself. Through this wound, his infinite host shall pour forth, drowning Azeroth in darkness.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "body_text": "Averzian uses [Shadow's Advance] to claim territory on the battlefield. Territory claimed cannot be retaken, and if Averzian claims three adjacent territories in a row he unleashes the [March of the Endless].\r\n\r\nCausing an [Umbral Collapse] on a territory being taken prevents its capture.",
      "spell": null,
      "sections": [
        {
          "title": "Damage Dealers",
          "body_text": "$bullet; Abyssal Voidshapers attempt to use [Gathering Darkness] at full power.\r\n$bullet; Shadowguard Stalwarts attempt to empower their allies with [Pitch Bulwark].",
          "spell": null,
          "sections": null
        },
        {
          "title": "Healers",
          "body_text": "$bullet;[Dark Upheaval] inflicts periodic damage to all players.\r\n$bullet;[Umbral Collapse] inflicts damage to everyone that is reduced by the number of players at the impact location.",
          "spell": null,
          "sections": null
        },
        {
          "title": "Tanks",
          "body_text": "$bullet; Averzian gains [Void Claimed] while close to ground he controls.\r\n$bullet; When Averzian strikes his current target he infects them with [Blackening Wounds].",
          "spell": null,
          "sections": null
        }
      ]
    },
